children.content: Healthcare clinics in the Dallas/Fort Worth area

From the moment you call our office, you will be treated with the level of care you expect from a provider. We treat patients of all ages, we want you and your family to remain healthy and active. We truly care about the health of every patient! We even offer chronic care management for chronic conditions.

Our all-encompassing health care services ensure you receive the correct diagnosis and treatment for any condition. This includes providing our patients and families with urgent care, primary injury care, travel health, wellness exams in Dallas, TX, and much more.

We are a group of healthcare clinics in the Dallas/Fort Worth area providing patients of all ages with the wellness care and services they need to remain healthy and active. Our all-encompassing health care services ensure you receive the correct diagnosis and treatment for any condition. This includes providing our patients and families with urgent care, primary injury care, travel health, wellness exams in Dallas, TX, and much more.

For the convenience of our clients, our services are offered on a walk-in basis — no appointments are needed. This ensures we can help relieve your symptoms as soon as possible, especially when your activities of daily living are affected. Discover more about us and our health care services in Dallas, TX, by reviewing the information we’ve provided on our website.

Contact us at one of our six healthcare clinics in Dallas and Fort Worth to speak with medical professionals about your care options. We feature treatment plans and programs for patients throughout the area. If you have any questions, please don’t hesitate to contact us.
We have six locations to serve you.
Same Day Appointments are Available. We also offer 24/7 chronic care management.
1324 N. Galloway Ave   Ste. 104   Mesquite, Texas 75149
Haresh Boghara, MD, MBA   Medical Director of CareFirst Primary and Wellness
Dr. Boghara has practiced medicine in Texas since 2012. His medical experience includes time as a Primary Care, Urgent Care and Emergency Physician, as well as work as a Hospitalist.

He has practiced medicine in a number of locations during this career, including Texas, North Carolina, Kentucky, and his native India. Dr. Boghara graduated at the top of his class in medical school.

His certifications include the American Board of Family Medicine, BLS, ACLS, ATLS, and PALS. He has served as a Medical Director in multiple hospital systems and most recently was part of the Dallas market for WELLMED Medical Management. He enjoys taking care of all age group patients and has a special interest in clinical trials. He enjoys outdoor activities and traveling in his free time.

Paul Schorr, D.O. is Board Certified in Family Practice and earned his Doctor of Osteopathic Post Graduate Fellowship in Family Practice from the University of Texas Southwest Medical School. He has practiced medicine for over 40 years of which 22 years in the Mesquite Community.

He is a designated Doctor with the Texas Workers Comp Board and a Public Safety Officer with the Texas Department of Public Safety. Dr. Schorr is on staff with Baylor Medical Center and Dallas Regional Hospital.

Dr. Mony earned her medical degree from India in 1997. After gaining clinical experience in India she relocated to the U.S. She completed her Family Medicine residency in 2008 at The Brooklyn Hospital Center, an affiliate of Weill Medical College of Cornell University. Dr Mony is a board-certified Family Physician, a member of the American Academy of Family Physicians, Texas Medical Association and Dallas County Medical Society. She has been practicing in the Dallas area for the last ten years.

Dr. Mony is a strong advocate of Preventive Medicine and spends time with her patients discussing the importance of a healthy lifestyle. She is committed to providing quality, evidence-based care to all her patients. She lives in Frisco with her husband and two sons. She enjoys listening to music, playing badminton, cricket and spending time with her family.
Dr. Quemado earned her Medical Degree in 2016 and serves as the Clinical Coordinator for CareFirst Primary’s Allergy program and Director of Weight Loss Management.

As Clinic Coordinator she has delivered an incredible patient experience with safe and efficacious clinical outcomes. This includes the administration of quality allergy testing, and the formulation and preparation of the allergy immunotherapy. Educating patients on proper administration of immunotherapy injections as well as advocating for strong compliance throughout their treatment plan. For three years, Dr. Quemado and CareFirst Primary have managed the Allergy program with over 700 patients.

During her spare time, Dr. Quemado enjoys volunteering at her favorite charity organizations, traveling and anything involving creativity. She is also obsessed with Harry Potter and has two cats and one dog named after her favorite characters.

Roy has been a Physician Assistant for 35 years. He graduated for UT Health Science Center-Dallas in 1985. Roy has practiced medicine his entire career in Texas. He has always had a passion for primary care. This started with the training in school where he and fellow classmates were geared toward primary care and rural medicine.
Roy brings a well rounded skill set to this practice. He is comfortable seeing pediatric and geriatric patients and is bilingual in Spanish and English.

Roy was raised in El Paso and has lived in most areas of the state but has called the Dallas area home for the last 13 years. He enjoys practicing Taekwondo and has done so for 10 years. Roy achieved the rank of 2nd degree/2nd Dan Black Belt. Not only is Roy an student he is also a referee at taekwondo tournaments.

At a young age, Vimi had a passion for helping others and showed a genuine interest in medicine. Through multiple high school societies, clubs and volunteer opportunities, Vimi found her fit in medicine by becoming a physician assistant and decided to a pursue a career in that area of medicine. She completed her Bachelor of Science in Biology from the University of Texas at Arlington and then further completed her Master of Physician Assistant Studies from MCPHSU in Boston, MA. After graduating with her Masters in 2014, she became a nationally certified physician assistant and has been an active member of the American Academy of Physician Assistants (AAPA). She is also ACLS and BLS certified.

She has been working in Internal Medicine and Family Medicine since graduating and is a strong advocate for Preventative medicine and health maintenance. She believes in partnering with the patient towards a common goal of achieving physical and psychological well-being through patient education and empowerment. She thoroughly enjoys educating and spending time with her patients by discussing how to manage chronic diseases by promoting healthy habits in order to achieve a good quality of life for years to come. She is committed to providing quality, evidence-based care to all of her patients.

She is a native Texan who has several interests from exploring the world through traveling, to performing cultural dances, to cuddling up with a good book in her free time. She enjoys spending quality time with her family and friends. She is an avid follower of Dallas sports teams and cheers for the Dallas Cowboys on NFL game day.

Bari is Certified Family Nurse Practitioner by the American Association of Nurse Practitioner by the American Association of Nurse Practitioners (AANC). She earned her Bachelor and Master of Science in Nursing from the Thomas Jefferson University in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. Bari also completed a Bachelor of Science in Human Sciences with concentration in Health Sciences, Nutrition and Addictive Disorders and Recovery Studies from Texas Tech University in Lubbock.

With an engaging smile, Bari believes that relationships and education are the key to providing top notch primary care. She is an educator at heart and practices preventative medicine to ensure her patients are armed with knowledge to maintain total body health. Her passion for providing primary care across the lifespan is matched by her interest in managing chronic illness, addictive medicine and occupational health including treating injuries. Bari is certified to provide medical clearance to individuals to obtain their commercial driver license through the Texas Department of Transportation.

Bari lives in Dallas with her cat Babka. In her spare time, she loves watching sports. Her beloved Chicago Cubs, Texas Rangers, Dallas Mavericks and Chicago Bears provide interesting conversation starters. She’s also a US History buff; ask her about any US president!
Nikki Dione Powell RN, MSN, FNP-C

Nikki Powell is a Certified Family Nurse Practitioner by the American Association of Nurse Practitioners (AANP). She earned her Bachelor of Science in Nursing from West Texas A & M and graduated Magna Cum Laude and her Master of Science in Nursing from the University of Cincinnati and graduated Summa Cum Laude.

Nikki has a strong commitment to compassionate care of her patients and an engaging personality that endears her patients to her. She loves her job and the patients and it shows when interacting. She has two young beautiful daughters that she loves to spend quality time with and they are her world.

Erica Diaz RN, MSN, FNP-C, is a certified Family Nurse Practitioner by the American Association of Nurse Practitioners (AANP). She obtained her Bachelors in nursing from Texas Woman’s University in 2010. As an undergraduate, Erica obtained the following accolades and memberships: National Honor Society, National Honor Scholar and the National Dean’s List. She worked in the emergency department at a Level II trauma center for 9 years where she received many certifications. Her certifications include BLS/ACLS CERTIFIED PALS, TNCC, Certification in Fundamental Critical Care Nursing Course, Certified Stroke Assessment Nurse and Certified Sexual Assault Nurse Examiner.

Erica was recognized as a Top Nurse by the Texas Nurses Association. She returned to complete her Masters of Science in Nursing at Texas Woman’s University and graduated just months shy of delivering her second child in a home birth.

She loves to spend time with family and is an avid Cowboys fan. She is the proud daughter of immigrants and is fluent in both English and Spanish. Erica also met Former President George W. Bush and spoke with Former President Barack Obama during the Ebola outbreak of 2014. She enjoys being an advocate for her patients and enjoys being a familiar face to them.

Dr. Rizkal was born in Los Angeles in 1983 and moved to the Dallas Fort Worth Metroplex in 1988. He began his pre-med studies at Texas Tech University in 2001 and was accepted by Parker University in 2004. Dr. Matt completed his Doctor of Chiropractic Degree & B.A. in Health and Wellness (Cum Laude) in 2007. He has been enjoying Physical Rehabilitation and Chiropractic practice ever since. Dr. Matt uses a wellness-based approach when taking care of patients. By combining the very best hands-on-technique, state of the art physiotherapy procedures, and offering guidance in healthy life-style choices, he is able to help his patients accelerate and maintain the journey to good health.

Dr. Matt enjoys staying active both physically and in the community. A few of his interests include softball, weightlifting, playing guitar, reading and college sports. Dr. Matt also participates in volunteer work to educate the public on healthy living and wellness in general. He has dedicated his life to promoting health and wellness to his patients and the public.

He is skilled in several Chiropractic and Physical Rehabilitation techniques including Diversified, Thompson, Flexion- Distraction, Activator, Trigger Point Therapy, and Proprioceptive Neuromuscular Facilitation.
